<div xmlns:java="http://xml.apache.org/xslt/java" id="centre_col"><!-- begin original content --><h1>ESSUM36250 - Exchange of share
options: Equivalent options</h1>
<br>
<p>Paragraph 39(3) requires the new options to be "equivalent" to
the old options, but relating to shares in a different company,
provided they satisfy paragraph 18(b) or (c). This means that there
must remain a "control" link, either directly or through a
consortium, between the company which established the scheme and
the company into whose shares the options are to be rolled over.
<br>
<br> "Equivalent" is not defined in the legislation, but
paragraph 39(4) provides that the new options will not be
equivalent unless the four tests in sub-paragraphs (a) to (d) are
satisfied.</p>
<br>
<ol type="a" start="1">
<li>Relates to the nature of the shares that can be the subject of
the new options. The new options must be over shares which satisfy
paragraphs 18-22. It may therefore be necessary to examine the
Articles of Association of the company whose shares are to be the
new scheme shares, particularly if the new shares are in an
unlisted company.
<br>
<br>
</li>
<li>Relates to the exercise provisions of the new options. The new

options must be exercisable in the same manner as the old options

and in accordance with the rules of the scheme before the rollover

took place. In particular this means that the times and triggers

for exercising the new options must be the same as applied to the

old options. (See 

<a href="ESSUM36260.htm">ESSUM36260</a>).

<br>
<br>
</li>
<li>Relates to the number of shares that will be the subject of the

new options. The total market value, immediately before the

rollover, of the shares subject to the old options, must be equal

to the market value of the shares subject to the new options at the

date the new options are granted in exchange. It is this

requirement which enables the number of shares under the new option

to be determined. (See 

<a href="ESSUM36270.htm">ESSUM36270</a>).

<br>
<br>
</li>
<li>Relates to the price at which the new options may be exercised.

The total aggregate exercise price to be paid for the shares by an

option-holder under the new option must be equal to the aggregate

exercise price relating to the shares which were the subject of the

old option. As the number of shares under the new option has

already been determined under (c), this requirement enables the

price at which the shares may be acquired under the new option, to

be determined. (See 

<a href="ESSUM36280.htm">ESSUM36280</a>).</li>
</ol>
